The fighter closed in on the Maximal base.  It pulled up, and transformed.  Its two engine sections straighten out, forming feminine legs ending feet.  It's feet were that like high heels.  The waist rotated 180 degrees, the two projections off the sides racheted forward, the landing claw folding back, hands pushed rom the wrists, forming the arms.  The nose completely detached, the smooth rounde section atache to the left forearm, making a sheild.  The very end of the nose was the sword of this hunter, in its ightful place, the ight hand.  The head popped from the shoulders and spun around.  The optics lit, and Organics decended.
"I am Organics.  I am a bounty hunter, I have searche the known univese, and now I have found that which I seek here.  Please send out Neutronics."

--- In nbwrpg@yahoogroups.com, robert riley <bustercross365@y...> 
wrote:
> Through a rift in space and time, a lone small spacecraft 
emerged.  It was really a fighter with a long range booster.  It 
came online and accessed the booster's long range sensors.  It 
detected several things: multiple bases planet side, and the looming 
Unicron in high orbit.  The craft banke, and made way for the far 
side of the planet, away from Unicron.  It skimmed across the 
atmosphere and then entered the atmosphere.  It was going to come 
down somewhee between all the bases.  After re-entry, the booster 
section jetisoned and the fighter spread its wings and touched off 
the engines.  It was then it detected the signal it was looking 
for.  It was coming fom a base with many Maximal signatures.
> <I have found him!  At long last, I found him!>
> It altered course and bee- lined for the Maximal base.  
> 
> 
> "In the name of God, I banish these souls of the evil undead into 
damnation.  May God have mercy, for I have none.  In Jesus' Holy 
Name, Amen." -Rawl, Hellsing-RPG
